      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <th scope="row">Wrestling Stance</th>
          <td
            ><ul>
              <li>
                As you move, keep your center of gravity between your legs and
                your weight going straight down (don’t overcommit your weight to
                either leg)
              </li>
              <li>
                A low stance (your head lower than your opponent’s head) is
                better for both offense and defense
              </li>
              <li>
                Standing tall is mainly for when you want to bait your opponent
                into attacking (e.g., if you’re great at defense)
              </li>
            </ul>
          </td>
        </tr>

        <tr>
          <th scope="row">Double Leg Takedown</th>
          <td
            ><ul>
              <li>
                Breakfall: Hang onto your opponent by holding their hip with
                your top hand and folding your chest onto their back. Soften
                your fall with your other arm, reaching it out far (keeping it
                too close may cause injury) and then slapping the ground with
                the first arm.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </td>
        </tr>
